OL,3,CPlans to pave Broad Street criticised
OL,4,Cover accessibility issues
OL,6,FPlans to fully pedestrianise a main
OL,7,Fstreet have been released, but there
OL,8,Fare concerns about the future of its
OL,9,Fexisting bus stop and disabled parking.
OL,11,F's plans would see Broad Street
OL,12,Fpermanently closed to traffic to
OL,13,Fcreate a community space, citing the
OL,14,Fsuccess of Charing Cross.
OL,16,FHowever, paving the area would mean
OL,17,Fthe removal of the local bus stop,
OL,18,Fwhich covers four routes and more than
OL,19,F60 bus journeys every weekday.
